            <p>PRINTING AND PUBLISHING HOUSE&#44;<lb/>
                No. 169 ELM STREET.<lb/>
                Office of Block &#38; Co.<lb/></p>
            <p>PRINTERS&#44;<lb/>
                PUBLISHERS&#44;<lb/>
                BOOKSELLERS&#44;<lb/>
                LITHOGRAPHERS&#44;<lb/>
                AND STATIONERS.</p>							
            <p>Cincinnati&#44; February 2 1880<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr. Morais<lb/>
                Philadelphia Pa<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>Please permit us to suggest that a volume<lb/> of select sermons would be of great benefit to less favored ministers<lb/> as well as lay men&#44; who wish to inform themselves on Jewish<lb/> theology.  Believing this to be the case we intend to publish such<lb/> a collection under the title of &#34;The American Jewish Pulpit&#34;¬ù<lb/> and will accept the productions of only the most distinguished<lb/> rabbis of this country.  Permit us to ask of you one of your<lb/> sermons such as you would wish to publish and also to give<lb/> us the privilege of publishing it in the above collection.  Should<lb/> you be willing to grant our request please give us the topic<lb/> of your sermon before writing it as we wish to prevent<lb/> duplication.  Hoping to hear from you at an early date&#44;<lb/> we have the honor of subscribing ourselves.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your Most Obedient Servants<lb/>
                Block &#38; Co.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
